{{Infobox football biography | name= Dagoberto Portillo | fullname = Dagoberto Portillo Gamero | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1979|11|16}} | birth_place = [[San Salvador]], [[El Salvador]] | height = {{convert|1.82|m|abbr=on}} | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1999–2001 | years2 = 2001–2003 | years3 = 2003–2004 | years4 = 2004–2006 | years5 = 2006–2008 | years6 = 2008–2009 | years7 = 2009–2010 | years8 = 2010–2011 | years9 = 2011–2013 | clubs1 = [[Alianza F.C.|Alianza]] | clubs2 = [[C.D. Luis Ángel Firpo|Luis Ángel Firpo]] | clubs3 = [[C.D. Chalatenango|Chalatenango]] | clubs4 = [[A.D. Isidro Metapán|Isidro Metapán]] | clubs5 = [[Alianza F.C.|Alianza]] | clubs6 = [[A.D. Isidro Metapán|Isidro Metapán]] | clubs7 = [[C.D. FAS|FAS]] | clubs8 = [[Once Municipal]] | clubs9 = [[CD Luis Angel Firpo|Luis Ángel Firpo]] | caps1 = | caps2 = | caps3 = | caps4 = | caps5 = | caps6 = 33 | caps7 = 33 | caps8 = | caps9 = 67 | goals1 = | goals2 = | goals3 = | goals4 = | goals5 = | goals6 = 1 | goals7 = 0 | goals8 = 3 | goals9 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 1995 | nationalyears2 = | nationalyears3 = | nationalyears4 = 2007–2013 | nationalteam1 = [[El Salvador national under-20 football team|El Salvador U20]] | nationalteam2 = [[El Salvador national under-21 football team|El Salvador U21]] | nationalteam3 = [[El Salvador national under-23 football team|El Salvador U23]] | nationalteam4 = [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] | nationalcaps1 = | nationalcaps2 = | nationalcaps3 = | nationalcaps4 = 11 | nationalgoals1 = | nationalgoals2 = | nationalgoals3 = | nationalgoals4 = 0 | pcupdate = 6 January 2011 | ntupdate = 9 February 2011 }}
{{spanish name 2|Portillo|Gamero}} '''Dagoberto Portillo Gamero''' (born November 16, 1979 in [[San Salvador]]) is a former [[El Salvador|Salvadoran]] [[Association football|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].
Portillo was also an active player internationally, playing for the [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador national team]].
==Career==
===Club=== He began his football career with [[Alianza F.C.|Alianza]] in 1999. In 2001, he transferred to [[C.D. Luís Ángel Firpo|Luís Ángel Firpo]] where he remained until 2003. That same year he was transferred to [[C.D. Chalatenango]], with whom he played for the Clausura 2004. For the Apertura 2004, he arrived at [[A.D. Isidro Metapán|Isidro Metapán]], for whom he played until 2006, until he rejoined with [[Alianza F.C.|Alianza]] again. For the Apertura 2008, Portillo returned to form part of the [[A.D. Isidro Metapán|Isidro Metapán]] squad. He later would go on to join [[C.D. FAS|FAS]] for the Apertura 2009 before leaving to [[Once Municipal]] for the [[Primera División de Fútbol Profesional - Apertura 2010|Apertura 2010]]. Though he returned to [[C.D. Luís Ángel Firpo|Luís Ángel Firpo]] for the 2011 season and has remained there ever since.
===International=== Dagoberto Portillo began his international career with [[El Salvador national under-20 football team|El Salvador's U20 national team]] in 1995. Through the years, he also went on to form part of the [[El Salvador national under-21 football team|El Salvador's U21]] and the [[El Salvador national under-23 football team|El Salvador's U23]]. He made his debut with the senior team in a March 2007 [[friendly match]] against [[Honduras national football team|Honduras]], under then coach [[Carlos de los Cobos]].<ref>[http://www.elgrafico.com/gol-nacional/primera/tabla-de-posiciones-apertura-2011/player/13/165.html El Grafico Profile] {{es icon}}</ref> During his career in the senior team, he has been injured numerous times; one game against Costa Rica in 2010 led him to the hospital.
On September 20, 2013, Portillo was one of 14 Salvadoran players banned for life due to their involvement with match fixing.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-24184567 |title= El Salvador match-fixing: 14 footballers banned for life |publisher= BBC |accessdate=21 September 2013}}</ref>
