'''Ilaro Stadium''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Ilaro]], [[Nigeria]]. Built in 2008, it is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is a home stadium for [[Gateway F.C.]]. The stadium has a capacity of 12,000 people. ==External links== *[http://www.ogunstate.gov.ng/ulnews3c.htm OGUN AWARDS CONTRACT FOR ILARO STADIUM (October 13, 2006)] *[http://thepmnews.com/2008/12/19/awolowo-athletics-meet-ends-today Awolowo Athletics meet ends today (December 19 2008)] *[http://www.ngrguardiannews.com/sports/article19//indexn3_html?pdate=050109&ptitle=Gateway%20opens%20stadium%20with%20victory%20over%20Kaduna%20&cpdate=050109 Gateway opens stadium with victory over Kaduna United]
