{{Infobox football biography | name = Lorenzo Tehau | image = | caption = | fullname = Lorenzo Tehau<ref>{{cite web|title=Squad lists for the FIFA Confederations Cup Brazil 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/02/10/38/80/fcclop_neutral.pdf|publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association (FIFA)|accessdate=20 June 2013|format=PDF|date=7 June 2013}}</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1989|04|10|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Tahiti]] | height = {{Height|m=1.76|precision=0}} | position = [[Forward (football)|Forward]], [[midfielder]] | currentclub = [[A.S. Central Sport]] | clubnumber = 23 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2009–2017 | clubs1 = [[AS Tefana]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2017– | clubs2 = [[A.S. Central Sport]] | caps2 = 2 | goals2 = 2 | nationalyears1 = 2010 | nationalteam1 = [[Tahiti national under-20 football team|Tahiti U-20]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | nationalyears2 = 2010– | nationalteam2 = [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]]<ref>{{NFT player|id=40051|accessdate=}}</ref> | nationalcaps2 = 20 | nationalgoals2 = 7 | club-update = | nationalteam-update = 20:18, 23 June 2013 (UTC) }}
'''Lorenzo Tehau''' is a footballer from [[Tahiti]] currently playing for [[A.S. Central Sport]]. He is the twin brother of [[Alvin Tehau]], brother of [[Jonathan Tehau]] and cousin of [[Teaonui Tehau]], all of them playing for [[Tahiti national football team]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Lorenzo Tehau |url=http://m.fifa.com/newscentre/news/newsid=1645331.html |title=Tahiti's Tehau boys leading the way - FIFA.com |website=M.fifa.com |date= |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref>
He represented his country in the [[2009 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] and now is a full-time member of the [[Tahiti national football team]]. He was the top goalscorer for Tahiti in the [[2012 OFC Nations Cup]], where his national side won the tournament for the first time.
