The '''Marghzar Cricket Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Islamabad]], Pakistan.<ref name="Cricinfo">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/columns/content/ground/58940.html |title=Marghzar Cricket Ground |accessdate=22 September 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> The first recorded match on the ground was in the 1988/89 season.<ref name="first">{{Cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/22/1492.html |title=Marghzar Cricket Ground |accessdate=22 September 2016 |work=Cricket Archive}}</ref> The ground has hosted more than forty [[first-class cricket|first-class]] matches since 1993.<ref name="FC">{{Cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/22/1492_f.html |title=First-Class Matches played on Marghzar Cricket Ground, Islamabad |accessdate=22 September 2016 |work=Cricket Archive}}</ref> It was selected as a venue to host a match in the [[2016–17 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]].<ref name="Quaid">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1047927.html |title=Pool B: Sui Northern Gas Pipelines Limited v National Bank of Pakistan at Islamabad, Nov 5-8, 2016  |accessdate=22 September 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref>

